   "body" : "This change allows to do\r\n```cpp\r\n[&](const RPCContext& ctx) -> UniValue`\r\n```\r\ninstead of\r\n```cpp\r\n[&](const RPCHelpMan& self, const JSONRPCRequest& request) -> UniValue\r\n```\r\nSo `RPCContext` ties `RPCHelpMan` and `JSONRPCRequest`. Then `ctx` is used to get actual parameter values. For instance, before:\r\n```cpp\r\nint timeout = 0;\r\nif (!request.params[0].isNull())\t\r\n    timeout = request.params[0].get_int();\r\n```\r\nand now\r\n```cpp\r\nint timeout = ctx.ParamOrDefault(0, int(0)).get_int();\r\n```\r\nIn this particular case removes the problematic second access to `request.params`.\r\n\r\nNote, currently draft, open for suggestions.",
